    The script compares the original ENST IDs from the HRT Atlas list with the Transcript stable IDs returned by BioMart. This was done to test whether ENST IDs were lost during mapping or whether the reduction from transcript-level entries to gene-level entries is mainly caused by multiple transcripts belonging to the same gene. In other words things got cluttered so more comprehensive tables were needed.
    The script created/updated 5 output tables stored in "data/processed/...":
        1. "hrt_atlas_human_hk_gene_lengths.tsv"
        Main gene-level output table. Contains one row per unique Ensembl Gene stable ID and adds the calculated "gene_length_bp" column.
        2. "hrt_atlas_transcripts_per_gene_mapping_qc.tsv"
        QC = qualit control table showing how many HRT Atlas transcript IDs map to each Ensembl Gene stable ID.
        3. "hrt_atlas_human_hk_genes_with_multiple_transcripts.tsv"
        Filtered QC table containing only genes with more than one corresponding HRT Atlas transcript.
        4. "hrt_atlas_unmapped_enst_from_biomart.tsv"
        Contains HRT Atlas ENST IDs from the original list that were not returned by BioMart.
        5. "hrt_atlas_enst_to_ensg_mapping_summary.tsv"
