Wrote the R Script "compare_humanHK_vsnonHK_hrt_gene_lengths.R" on 25.05.26 which reads the table "human_all_genes_with_hrt_atlas_hk_status_rescued.tsv" using the columns: Gene stable ID, Gene start (bp), Gene end (bp), Chromosome/scaffold name, gene_length_bp, hk_status.
    This script gives 3 Outputs: results/tables/human_hrt_gene_length_summary.tsv, results/figures/human_hrt_gene_length_boxplot.png, results/tables/human_hrt_gene_length_wilcox_test.tsv 
    Output 1contains descriptive statistics for HK and non-HK genes, including n, mean, median, sd, quartiles, IQR, min and max gene length in bp. 
    Output 2 shows the HK vs non-HK gene length distributions as a boxplotpng with log10-scaled y-axis (gene length sometimes skewed right).
    Output 3 ist a wilcox ranksumtest. It compares genelength values of HK genes against nonHK genes using rank distributions instead of directly comparing means. (Sensible because gene lengths are strongly skewed.)
    Key Findings: 
    human_hrt_gene_length_wilcox_test.tsv: HK genes showed a lower median gene length than non-HK genes. Wilcoxon rank-sum test: p = 3.27 × 10^-14.
    human_hrt_gene_length_summary.tsv: median HK = 22.800 bp, median non-HK = 28.549 bp     mean HK = 39.014 bp, mean nonHK = 72.910 bp.
